name: Janet Mills
tweet: Maine people deserve every ounce of hard-won progress that we have achieved.  Maine people have earned the progress that is yet to come.

name: Janet Mills
tweet: We are looking at a revenue surplus — and I am working to put that money back in your pockets.   Maine is on the right track, and I’m determined to keep it that way.   https://t.co/4Ipw2A88vb

name: Janet Mills
tweet: We have accomplished so much, but, today, I’m announcing that I’m running for reelection because there is so much left to do. It’s time to invest in you, the people of Maine. You are what moves us forward, what makes us strong.  https://t.co/7EawwR9lCT

name: Janet Mills
tweet: Maine is our home. Tomorrow we rise before the dawn — like the mist over the Sandy River — and seek adventure, with hope in our hearts and love in our souls for the brand new day. To all of you, and to the people of Maine, I say, welcome home. Thank you. #mepolitics  https://t.co/SgLVq5adnu

name: Janet Mills
tweet: From the tree streets of Lewiston to the rolling fields of the County, from the Bold Coast to the Height of Land, from Cross Rock in Allagash to Portland’s Promenades, our people will once again find unity of purpose. #mepolitics

name: Janet Mills
tweet: My administration will create an Office of Innovation and the Future. This office will dive into major policy challenges, foster collaboration and propose concrete, workable solutions. Let's look ahead for a change. #mepolitics

name: Janet Mills
tweet: It is high time we put children’s health and safety first. I will start with one simple step —calling together the Children's Cabinet for the first time in years, to tackle these issues. #mepolitics
